About 5,000 leaders have endorsed Machakos Governor Alfred Mutua for President in 2022.The leaders, including governor, senator, MP and MCA hopefuls, said Mutua&rsquo;s star is rising beyond county politics.Mutua founded and heads the Maendeleo Chap Chap party.&ldquo;Machakos residents have a visionary leader whose agenda is beyond Ukambani politics,&rdquo; said Kanja Muchina, a Nyandarua county governor aspirant.Muchina said Mutua is the best bet for Ukambani to win the presidency in 2022. Kipipiri MP hopeful John Gachamba said Mutua is best-suited to assume the mantle once President Uhuru Kenyatta&rsquo;s second term ends in 2022.Machakos county assembly majority whip Timothy Kilonzo said Mutua is youthful with presidential potential.Mutua hosted the leaders at Machakos People&rsquo;s Park. He said he will continue providing &ldquo;transformative&rsquo; leadership at county and national levels.Mutua urged the voters to elect candidates running on his MCC party ticket. He assured the aspirants nominations will be free and fair.&ldquo;The party will give its tickets to the best, popular candidates,&rdquo; Mutua said The county chief criticised opposition leaders planning demonstrations over the new election law, saying their plot is retrogressive.&ldquo;These protests will scare away investors, leading to job losses. They will lead to anarchy and destruction of property,&rdquo; he said.However, the protest plan has apparently been shelved.Mutua will run for reelection on the MCC ticket. He said the party is not an affiliate of Jubilee or Cord, but will support Kenyatta&rsquo;s reelection.&ldquo;Uhuru and I share the same ideology of development. That&rsquo;s why I will back him for a second term,&rdquo; he said.Mutua said MCC will become one of the biggest political players, not only in Ukambani but also nationallyMasinga MP Itwiku Mbai and at least 30 Machakos MCAs were present.Mbai backed Mutua&rsquo;s reelection, saying he has initiated tangible development projects.On Saturday, Mutua visited Ol Kalou, Nyandarua county, to market MCC and meet supporters and aspirants.